Preheat your oven to 210°C and pop your @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a
#roasting tray{}, drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Roast on the top shelf of your oven for ~{18%minutes}, turning halfway.

Trim the @spring onion{1} then slice thinly. Trim the @cucumber{1/2} then halve
lengthways. Chop into roughly 1cm wide 5cm long batons. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the
@salted peanuts{25%g}(roughly chopped).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #pan{} on high heat, once hot, add the
@British pork mince{240%g} and cook until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}. Break it up
with a #wooden spoon{} as it cooks. Add the garlic and
@ginger puree{1}, cook for ~{1%minute}, stirring, then add the
@hoisin sauce{50%g} and @soy sauce{25%g} and cook for a further ~{2-3%minutes},
until sticky and reduced.

> IMPORTANT: The pork mince is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

About ~{2%minutes} before the potatoes are done, pop the
@plain taco tortillas{6} onto a #baking tray{} and bake until warmed through,
~{2%minutes}.

Warm the pork through if needed. Remove the sweet potato fries from the oven
once they are done.

Divide the pork mixture between the tacos and top with the cucumber,
spring onion and peanuts. Serve with the sweet potato fries. Enjoy!